==<span style="font-family:Kavivanar;">Description</span>==

'''Level 759''', otherwise known as Freeze Frame, is only rumored to exist, as only two people have claimed to encounter it. The level supposedly takes the appearance of a park at night, covered by a thick blanket of snow. The size of the level is unknown, but one of the surviving wanderers has claimed that it is roughly the size of a football field. A harsh snowstorm constantly descends on the level, making it dangerous to traverse without any equipment to shelter oneself from the cold.

Benches and lampposts covered in snow can be seen on the edges of a gravel walkway, with trees forming clusters around certain areas in the grass. An oddly placed tree stands tall in the middle of one walkway, its roots gripping into the gravel beneath. At times the snowstorm will subside, only leaving light snowfall behind. There are no pictures of this level, because the two survivors did not have cameras at the time, nor was it their top priority.

The most peculiar part of this level is that above the raging of the snowstorm, the distant ticking of a clock can be heard. It is unknown where the clock is located, but for every tick of the clock, wanderers can only move one step. In between ticks, they are frozen in place by an unknown force. Although unable to move, breathing and blinking are still permitted, albeit limited. An audio log of a [[M.E.G.]] agent interviewing a survivor will be provided, though the wanderer has requested to keep their identity anonymous.
==<span style="font-family:Kavivanar;">The Interview</span>==
<div class="darkblock">Interviewer: Stacy McNeil
<br>[AUDIO INTERVIEW BEGINS]

McNeil: Okay, begin whenever you're ready.

???: Okay, well, I was in [[Level 11]], visiting friends. I was leaving their apartment and headin' back when I suddenly felt a cold wind, like someone had turned on the AC, you know? So I look around, and I see a store called Freeze Frame, but the windows were, like, pure white. The door was open, but it looked like it had been frozen over. Seemed like a camera shop, from the name.

McNeil: Interesting. Is the store still there?

???: No, it's gone now. Probably disappeared after I entered it. Anyway, I was curious, and walked into the store. All I could feel was the cold at first, cause I wasn't wearing a jacket or anything. At first I couldn't move my body. Then, I could hear like, a clock ticking. When it ticked I was able to move for a brief moment, then I froze again. I could still blink and breathe, but my chest felt heavy.

McNeil: Okay... well, what did the level look like?

???: It looked like a park, but there was tons of snow everywhere. There was a snowstorm at first too, but it stopped after a while. Thank god, too, cause I was freezin' my ass off. The park was probably the size of, like, a football field maybe? I'm not sure.

Beyond the park it was just pitch black. Well, I could only take a step every time the clock ticked, so it was slow work. I was freezing my ass off, and my legs were tired. Eventually I got to this strange tree growing in the middle of the path, and when I touched it I got sent to [[Level 0]]. Shit was strange, I'm tellin' ya.

McNeil: Well, thank you for your information. How about I treat you to some grub for all your trouble?

[AUDIO INTERVIEW ENDS]
</div>
==<span style="font-family:Kavivanar;">Entities</span>==

{{Collapse|num=1|initial=<span style="color: var(--theme-link-color);">'''<span style="font-family:Mate SC;">To date, there are no entities on this level due to the lack of information.</span>|final=<span style="color: var(--theme-link-color);">'''<span style="font-family:Mate SC;">Don't forget us.</span></span>'''</span>|body=I remember the raging white of the snowstorm. The biting cold. The moment my heart stopped and my body hit the snow. I remember it all. Those two that made it out, I was with them. They didn't hear me over the screaming of the snow and because my vocal cords had frozen over, but I was urging them to fight on. To live.

I've seen too many of us fall victim to the level's design, some are with me right now, drifting aimlessly within the blinding white, unable to leave. Those among us with stronger wills left their souls behind, and we watched as our bodies sank into the soft snow, into the level to feed it.

The level is alive, and it's hungry. Don't forget us, please. As long as no one forgets, we may have a chance to leave. To live our lives once more. To escape the icy confines of the level. If we're forgotten, we'll freeze in time forever.{{Collapse|num=2|initial=<span style="color: var(--theme-link-color);">'''<span style="font-family:Qahiri;font-size:25px;">Please.</span>|final=<span style="color: var(--theme-link-color);">'''<span style="font-family:Qahiri;font-size:25px;">I feel myself freezing up already.</span>'''</span>|body=There is another way to leave this domain. Submerge yourself in the snow. It may seem counter-intuitive, but the snow is key. Every tick of the clock counts down the time you have left to live. It doesn't matter how many layers you have on, or how resistant your body is to extreme temperatures, everyone has the same amount of time to leave. 120 ticks. Two minutes. Two minutes to leave, to escape.

Yes, the tree works, but it may not always be close enough. Sink into the snow, it's your only chance to survive. Close your eyes, and count to ten in your head. You'll wake up in [[Level 399|that place.]] Good luck, and please survive. For all of us that didn't.}}}}
==<span style="font-family:Kavivanar;">Bases, Outposts and Communities</span>==
Due to the dangers posed and difficulty of finding this level, bases are unable to be established. Because of this, it is ill-advised to go searching for this level, and should be done so at one's own discretion.

==<span style="font-family:Kavivanar;">Entrances and Exits</span>==
===<span style="font-family:Kavivanar;">Entrances</span>===
* Only one method of entry has been reported by both survivors, which is to find a store with pure-white windows and a door which is covered in ice on [[Level 11]], entering which will bring wanderers here.

===<span style="font-family:Kavivanar;">Exits</span>===
* Similarly, only one method of exit has been discovered, which is to touch a tree located in the middle of the gravel path to be sent to [[Level 0]].
